From: Sergey Fedorov <barracuda@macos-powerpc.org>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 14:16:29 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 29/67] docs(macos): feature roadmap for the native frontend

A grounded subset of upstream contour's features: color themes (dark/light),
minimal preferences (theme/font/encoding/terminal-id), standard Window menu,
full-screen (native + a 10.6 manual path), drag & drop, scrollback wheel scroll,
selection->copy, plus an OpenGL 2.0/2.1 render backend (sibling of the CPU
SoftwareRenderTarget, with runtime CPU fallback). Notes the pre-existing
uneven-spacing issue and that tabs/split panes are engine-supported (vtmux) but
frontend-deferred.

